0photo%20of%20the%20Radiohead%20front%20man%20Thom%20Yorke%20looking%20upset%2C%20with%20the%20caption%20%26quot%3BDON'T%20MAKE%20THOM%20ANGRY!%26quot%3B%20On%20and%20on%20went%20the%20increasingly%20caustic%20and%20chaotic%20memes%20as%20the%20national%20tragedy%20unfolded%20that%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20attacks%2C%20comedians%2C%20pundits%2C%20and%20citizens%20grappled%20with%20the%20nature%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarc-andreessen-thinks-ai-can-save-comedy-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomedy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20debated%20when%20it%20would%20be%20OK%20to%20make%20jokes%20even%20tangentially%20related%20to%20the%20collective%20horror%20experienced%20that%20day.%20What's%20politically%20correct%3F%20What's%20even%20funny%20anymore%3F%20Late-night%20talk%20shows%20suspended%20their%20programming%20for%20weeks%2C%20and%20when%20they%20came%20back%2C%20most%20were%20mournful%2C%20solemn%2C%20and%20tepid.%20On%20September%2029%2C%20Gilbert%20Gottfried%20was%20booed%20during%20a%20stand-up%20set%20after%20he%20joked%20that%20he%20couldn't%20get%20a%20direct%20flight%20to%20New%20York%20because%20the%20pilot%20had%20to%20stop%20over%20at%20the%20Empire%20State%20Building%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20discourse%20about%20what's%20OK%20to%20joke%20about%20and%20when%20it's%20OK%20to%20joke%20about%20it%20missed%20a%20crucial%20point.%20As%20those%20SomethingAwful%20posters%20demonstrated%20in%20watching%20and%20processing%20the%20events%20of%20September%2011%20in%20real%20time%2C%20everyday%20people%20were%20using%20the%20freewheeling%20language%20of%20the%20internet%20with%20little%20care%20about%20whether%20society%20felt%20it%20was%20gauche.%209%2F11%20was%20destined%20to%20become%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-ai-startup-viral-memes-wants-to-upend-the-market-for-compute-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ememe%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty-three%20years%20later%2C%20however%2C%209%2F11%20memes%20have%20become%20so%20diffuse%20and%20abstracted%20from%20the%20tragedy%2C%20and%20the%20people%20creating%20and%20sharing%20them%20too%20young%20to%20remember%209%2F11%20as%20it%20happened%2C%20that%20a%20crucial%20question%20has%20emerged%3A%20What%20does%209%2F11%20even%20mean%20to%20the%20internet%20anymore%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20%26quot%3Bunsinkable%26quot%3B%20Titanic%20sank%20and%20claimed%20more%20than%201%2C500%20lives%20on%20April%2015%2C%201912%2C%20it%20made%20newspaper%20headlines%20around%20the%20world.%20It%20was%20a%20nightmarish%20tragedy%20that%20shocked%20humanity's%20psyche.%20Within%20two%20weeks%2C%20the%20first%20Titanic%20joke%20had%20already%20been%20logged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20short%20story%20dated%20April%2028%2C%201912%2C%20the%20Czech%20humorist%20Jaroslav%20Ha%C5%A1ek%20quipped%20that%20the%20ship%20sank%20because%20its%20passengers%20%26quot%3Bwere%20not%20praying%20on%20its%20board%20throughout%20the%20voyage%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThey%20did%20so%20only%20when%20the%20ship%20was%20sinking%20but%20God%20punished%20them%2C%20it%20was%20too%20late.%26quot%3B%20The%20iceberg%20the%20ship%20struck%2C%20however%2C%20%26quot%3Bprayed%20and%20so%20nothing%20happened%20to%20it.%26quot%3B%20%3Cem%3EBa%20dum%20tss%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Ha%C5%A1ek%20was%20far%20from%20alone.%20In%20a%202019%20essay%20for%20the%20International%20Journal%20of%20Humor%20Research%2C%20the%20Czech%20linguistics%20scholar%20Jan%20Chovanec%20chronicled%20dozens%20of%20jokes%20and%20cartoons%20printed%20around%20the%20world%20in%20the%20tragedy's%20immediate%20wake%2C%20including%20the%20canned%20joke%20about%20the%20guy%20who%20complains%20about%20the%20price%20of%20his%20lobster%20only%20for%20his%20waiter%20to%20say%20it%20was%20found%20near%20the%20site%20of%20the%20Titanic%20wreckage%2C%20so%2C%20who%20knows%2C%20there%20could%20be%20diamonds%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3Ea%20second%20coconut%20has%20hit%20the%20context%20of%20all%20in%20which%20you%20live%20and%20what%20came%20before%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20marina%20%F0%9F%8C%9E%20(%40marinadovexo)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmarinadovexo%2Fstatus%2F1815090567749255521%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2021%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20neither%20of%20these%20jokes%20from%20a%20century%20ago%20is%20funny%20by%20today's%20standards%2C%20they%20and%20the%20dozens%20of%20others%20Chovanec%20found%20are%20similar%20to%209%2F11%20jokes.%20Much%20of%20the%20dialogue%20on%20post-9%2F11%20humor%20has%20focused%20on%20its%20power%20and%20intent%20to%20cope%20with%20grief.%20The%202021%20documentary%20%26quot%3BToo%20Soon%3A%20Comedy%20After%209%2F11%26quot%3B%20features%20comedians%20breathlessly%20explaining%20how%20their%20craft%20helped%20the%20country%20heal%20and%20%26quot%3Bpush%20back%20terror.%26quot%3B%20But%20Giselinde%20Kuipers%2C%20a%20Dutch%20sociologist%20who%20has%20extensively%20studied%209%2F11-related%20internet%20humor%2C%20has%20found%20that%20disaster%20jokes%20are%20primarily%20made%20to%20entertain%20others%20%E2%80%94%20and%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20do%20that%20is%20to%20make%20light%20of%20an%20event%20everyone's%20familiar%20with.%209%2F11%20jokes%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20often%20have%20very%20little%20to%20do%20with%209%2F11.%20They're%20much%20more%20like%20Ha%C5%A1ek's%20strange%20joke%20about%20the%20iceberg%20praying%2C%20a%20way%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20world%20using%20a%20widely%20shared%20reference%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKuipers%20argues%20that%20while%20the%20nature%20of%20most%20disaster%20jokes%20hasn't%20changed%2C%20the%20difference%20is%20that%209%2F11%20happened%20to%20occur%20during%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20social%20internet%2C%20when%20this%20once%20hard-to-find%2C%20%26quot%3Bvery%20specific%2C%20niche%20kind%20of%20dark%20humor%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20became%20very%20accessible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhitney%20Phillips%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20digital%20platforms%20and%20ethics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Oregon%2C%20says%20that%20when%20major%20disasters%20occur%2C%20something%20called%20%26quot%3Bappropriate%20incongruity%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20perfect%20mashup%20of%20unrelated%20things%20%E2%80%94%20takes%20hold%20in%20online%20communication.%20%26quot%3BWith%20September%2011%20humor%2C%20you%20saw%20a%20lot%20of%20references%20to%20the%20Kool-Aid%20Man%20bursting%20through%20the%20towers%20or%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2F53gaDr3amca5t%2Fstatus%2F1812709159525061092%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3EHulk%20Hogan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20other%20cultural%20touchstones%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Hulk%20Hogan%20%26quot%3Bis%20so%20far%20removed%20from%20a%20terrorist%20attack%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added%2C%20that%20the%20joke%20is%20simply%20the%20outrageousness%20connecting%20the%20two%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20appropriate%20incongruity%20happens%20time%20and%20time%20again.%20When%20Donald%20Trump%20was%20shot%20in%20the%20ear%20on%20July%2013%2C%20for%20example%2C%20X%20and%20Instagram%20were%20flooded%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fthe_okayest_computer%2Fp%2FC9YeoyevcDB%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ememes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20Claire's%2C%20the%20ear-piercing%20store%20ubiquitous%20in%201990s%20and%202000s%20shopping%20malls.%20Why%20do%20we%20do%20these%20things%3F%20In%20part%20because%20we%20can.%20%26quot%3BWhatever%20your%20motivation%20would%20be%2C%20if%20it%20wasn't%20so%20easy%20to%20do%20it%2C%20people%20wouldn't%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Phillips%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20about%20memes%20is%20that%20they%20add%20layers%20of%20abstraction%20to%20the%20original%20thing%20they%20reference%20%E2%80%94%20until%20they're%20either%20meaningless%20or%20full%20of%20meaning%20but%20meaning%20something%20altogether%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20most%20pervasive%209%2F11%20meme%20of%20recent%20years%20is%20a%20simple%20one%2C%20a%20riff%20on%20one%20of%20the%20defining%20images%20of%20the%2021st%20century.%20It's%20the%20photo%20taken%20during%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush's%20visit%20to%20a%20Florida%20elementary%20school%20showing%20the%20White%20House%20chief%20of%20staff%20Andrew%20Card%20whispering%20the%20news%20of%20a%20second%20plane%20hitting%20the%20twin%20towers%20to%20Bush%2C%20who%20stares%20wide-eyed%20ahead%20off%20camera.%20I%20see%20this%2023-year-old%20image%20almost%20every%20single%20day%20on%20Reddit%20and%20X.%20Perhaps%20second%20only%20to%20my%20own%20in%20the%20mirror%2C%20Bush's%20face%20in%202001%20is%20the%20face%20I%20see%20most%20often%20in%202024.%20The%20image%20is%20typically%20coupled%20with%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Ba%20second%20%5Bthing%5D%20has%20hit%20%5Bsomething%20else%5D.%26quot%3B%20It%20might%20be%20about%20Kamala%20Harris'%20idiosyncratic%20aphorisms%3A%20%26quot%3BA%20second%20coconut%20has%20hit%20the%20context%20of%20all%20in%20which%20you%20live%20and%20what%20came%20before.%26quot%3B%20Or%20about%20JD%20Vance's%20college%20years%3A%20%26quot%3BSir%2C%20a%20second%20JD%20Vance%20drag%20photo%20has%20hit%20the%20internet.%26quot%3B%20Or%20about%20the%20sculpted%20star%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Bear%26quot%3B%20posing%20in%20his%20underwear%3A%20%26quot%3BSir%2C%20a%20second%20Jeremy%20Allen%20White%20Calvin%20Klein%20campaign%20has%20hit%20the%20internet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20photo%20is%20now%20so%20seared%20into%20the%20brains%20of%20the%20terminally%20online%20that%20it%20sometimes%20requires%20no%20caption%20at%20all.%20Over%20the%20weekend%2C%20when%20the%20rapper%20Kendrick%20Lamar%20announced%20he%20would%20perform%20in%20the%20Super%20Bowl%20halftime%20show%2C%20%40DDotOmen%20posted%20a%20stand-alone%20photo%20of%20Card%20whispering%20in%20the%20ear%20of%20not%20Bush%20but%20Lamar's%20vanquished%20rap-beef%20adversary%2C%20Drake.%20The%20idea%20of%20context%20collapse%20is%20often%20derided%20as%20a%20negative%20effect%20of%20the%20modern%20web%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20the%20engine%20that's%20allowed%20abstract%20humor%20to%20become%20the%20memetic%20language%20of%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSeinfeld%26quot%3B%20had%20been%20off%20the%20air%20for%20more%20than%20three%20years%20on%209%2F11%2C%20but%20Billy%20Domineau%20knew%20exactly%20how%20Jerry%2C%20Elaine%2C%20George%2C%20and%20Kramer%20would%20have%20reacted.%20In%202016%2C%20the%20superfan%20published%20%26quot%3BThe%20Twin%20Towers%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20masterful%20spec%20script%20that%20imagines%20the%20nihilistic%20quartet%20in%20the%20days%20after%20the%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeorge%2C%20ever%20an%20opportunist%2C%20is%20mistaken%20for%20a%20first%20responder%20and%20gladly%20accepts%20the%20undeserved%20hero's%20honor.%20Elaine%20learns%20that%20her%20latest%20beau%20perished%20in%20the%20towers%20but%20accepts%20it%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20gonna%20break%20up%20with%20him%20anyway.%26quot%3B%20She%20then%20learns%2C%20to%20her%20dismay%2C%20that%20he%20survived%20and%20she's%20stuck%20with%20him.%20Jerry%20is%20annoyed%20and%20grossed%20out%20by%20the%20dust%20he%20sees%20everywhere%20in%20the%20city%20%E2%80%94%20in%20his%20food%2C%20in%20a%20date's%20teeth.%20Kramer%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20irate%20that%20he%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20get%20back%20the%20prized%20box%20cutter%20he%20loaned%20to%20his%20%26quot%3Bcrazy%20friend%20Mo%20Atta.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDomineau%20told%20me%20that%209%2F11%20was%20an%20entirely%20humorless%20affair%20for%20him%20as%20a%20middle%20schooler%20in%20the%20Boston%20suburbs.%20He%20remembers%20being%20completely%20overwhelmed%2C%20refusing%20to%20watch%20news%20coverage%20of%20it%20that%20night%20and%20instead%20putting%20on%20a%20VHS%20of%20%26quot%3BHappy%20Gilmore%26quot%3B%20to%20dissociate.%20He%20wrote%20the%20script%2C%20he%20says%2C%20not%20to%20make%20light%20of%20or%20even%20offer%20commentary%20on%20the%20disaster%20but%20simply%20as%20a%20way%20of%20%26quot%3Bplaying%20with%20the%20limits%20of%20'Seinfeld'%20itself%2C%20the%20tropes%20of%20the%20series%2C%20and%20the%20characters%20as%20we%20know%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20had%20lofty%20goals%20for%20it%2C%20hoping%20it%20might%20help%20him%20break%20into%20the%20world%20of%20professional%20comedy%20writing.%20Despite%20some%20chatter%20about%20whether%2015%20years%20later%20was%20still%20too%20soon%20and%20whether%20it%20was%20written%20in%20bad%20taste%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Twin%20Towers%26quot%3B%20went%20viral%2C%20received%20glowing%20reviews%2C%20and%20eventually%20helped%20land%20Domineau%20a%20writing%20job%20on%20%26quot%3BSaturday%20Night%20Live.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20highest%20compliment%20he%20received%20was%20from%20another%20comedian%2C%20Dan%20Gregor%2C%20who%20tweeted%2C%20as%20Domineau%20paraphrases%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20this%20had%20come%20out%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%209%2F11%2C%20we%20could%20have%20avoided%20the%20Iraq%20War.%26quot%3B%20Domineau%20feels%20that%20when%20tragedies%20are%20treated%20like%20sacred%20cows%2C%20when%20we%20as%20a%20society%20don't%20allow%20humor%20to%20allow%20us%20to%20heal%2C%20we%20dangerously%20relinquish%20control.%20If%20we're%20not%20allowed%20to%20laugh%20at%20our%20collective%20trauma%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bbasically%20the%20government%20just%20owns%20the%20rights%20to%20both%20talking%20about%20the%20issue%20and%20deciding%20how%20we'll%20respond%20to%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Domineau%20or%20those%20anonymous%20SomethingAwful%20posters%2C%20many%20people%20making%20and%20spreading%209%2F11%20memes%20today%20are%20too%20young%20to%20remember%209%2F11%2C%20if%20they%20were%20alive%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3Ethe%20horses%20in%20this%20game%20are%20so%20beautiful%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FTearsoftheKingdom%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23TearsoftheKingdom%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fk7KJOjFTFG%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fk7KJOjFTFG%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20%F0%9F%92%99ambi%E2%98%81%EF%B8%8F%20(%40aquatic_ambi)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Faquatic_ambi%2Fstatus%2F1815800891368493242%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2023%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%2023-year-old%20from%20Las%20Vegas%20who%20goes%20by%20the%20X%20handle%20%40aquatic_ambi%20posted%20to%20her%2015%2C000%20followers%20a%20video%20she%20made%20from%20a%20%26quot%3BLegend%20of%20Zelda%26quot%3B%20game%20with%20the%20caption%20%26quot%3Bthe%20horses%20in%20this%20game%20are%20so%20beautiful.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20video's%20foreground%2C%20the%20player's%20character%20walks%20toward%20a%20horse%2C%20while%20in%20the%20background%20a%20flying%20machine%20crashes%20into%20one%20of%20two%20makeshift%20towers%20in%20a%20fireball%20explosion.%20The%20post%20has%20received%20more%20than%20245%2C000%20likes.%20She%20says%209%2F11%20memes%20have%20always%20been%20popular%20with%20her%20cohort.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20always%20tend%20to%20make%20humor%20in%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20just%20an%20easy%20joke%20to%20make%20since%20two%20towers%20are%20an%20instantly%20recognizable%20thing%20and%20easy%20to%20portray%20in%20memes.%26quot%3B%20She%20posted%20the%209%2F11%20video%20only%20after%20another%20irreverent%20meme%20of%20hers%20found%20success%20on%20the%20site.%20%26quot%3BI%20made%20a%20JFK%20assassination%20video%20in%20'Zelda%2C'%20and%20a%20comment%20requested%20I%20do%20a%209%2F11%20one%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20assumed%20it%20had%20already%20been%20done%2C%20so%20I%20never%20thought%20to%20do%20one%20until%20then.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDomineau%20says%20it's%20only%20natural%20for%20young%20people%20to%20take%209%2F11%20jokes%20to%20the%20next%20extreme.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20inherit%20a%20piece%20of%20cultural%20trauma%20that%20you%20weren't%20alive%20for%2C%20there's%20a%20numbness%20or%20lack%20of%20appreciation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20always%20been%20on%20the%20table%20to%20play%20around%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20ways%2C%20that%20play%20is%20a%20vital%20sign%20of%20America's%20resilience%20and%20resolve.%20But%20it%20also%20underscores%20the%20need%20to%20teach%20subsequent%20generations%20what%20happened%20and%20what%20it%20felt%20like%20for%20those%20who%20experienced%20it.%20As%20Domineau%20puts%20it%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20need%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20history%20of%209%2F11%20in%20detail%20so%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bcan%20hopefully%20%E2%80%94%20to%20some%20extent%20%E2%80%94%20be%20as%20shocked%20and%20horrified%20as%20people%20who%20were%20already%20living%20in%20the%20world%20when%20it%20happened.%26quot%3B%20Otherwise%2C%20%26quot%3BNever%20Forget%26quot%3B%20just%20becomes%20another%209%2F11%20meme.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fscott-nover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EScott%20Nover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20freelance%20writer%20based%20in%20Washington%2C%20