%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freceived-250000-inheritance-regret-how-spent-it-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einherited%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20four%20common%20questions%20they%20were%20concerned%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fa680825-c274-42f4-83cb-4d9a3a218cfa%5C%22%3E1.%20How%20can%20I%20determine%20what%20my%20family%20expects%20of%20me%20and%20what%20I%20can%20expect%20without%20seeming%20entitled%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rising%20generation%20wants%20to%20ensure%20they're%20honoring%20the%20hard%20work%20done%20by%20previous%20generations.%20But%20often%2C%20they%20aren't%20sure%20what%20success%20means%20to%20those%20people%2C%20perhaps%20because%20family%20members%20feel%20uncomfortable%20talking%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20rising%20generation%20members%20told%20us%20they%20feel%20like%20their%20parents%20are%20concerned%20that%20their%20wealth%20will%20impede%20their%20children's%20motivation%20and%20desire%20to%20thrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20encourage%20the%20rising%20generation%20to%20ask%20older%20generations%20what%20their%20vision%20is%20and%20how%20they%20see%20the%20wealth%20being%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20been%20working%20with%20a%20family%20for%20numerous%20years%3A%20The%20parents%20are%20first-generation%20wealth%20creators%2C%20and%20they%20have%20three%20young%20adult%20children%20who%20all%20worked%20hard%20and%20attended%20top%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20spoke%20with%20the%20children%20individually%2C%20one%20of%20them%20shared%20that%20she%20had%20a%20good%20job%20on%20paper%20as%20a%20corporate%20attorney%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20fulfilling%20for%20her%2C%20and%20she%20wanted%20to%20explore%20something%20entrepreneurial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20hadn't%20discussed%20what%20success%20and%20purpose%20meant%20for%20them%2C%20but%20when%20we%20spoke%20with%20the%20parents%2C%20they%20shared%20they%20wanted%20their%20kids%20to%20have%20the%20freedom%20to%20explore%20entrepreneurship%20and%20didn't%20want%20them%20to%20be%20in%20jobs%20that%20weren't%20fulfilling%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20opened%20up%20a%20conversation%20about%20what%20assets%20she%20could%20access%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-and-grow-a-business-founders-advice-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estart%20a%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20a%20dialogue%20across%20generations%20starts%2C%20it%20can%20be%20a%20wonderful%20way%20for%20the%20rising%20generation%20to%20understand%20what's%20expected%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20expectation%20will%20not%20be%20answered%20in%20one%20conversation%2C%20but%20starting%20the%20dialogue%20is%20critical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223a849921-befb-4f42-b1b1-459d8f240592%5C%22%3E2.%20How%20can%20I%20build%20my%20own%20personal%20identity%2C%20both%20within%20and%20outside%20the%20family%20wealth%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEngaging%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-family-business-peerless-coffee-unsure-kids-should-follow-steps-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamily%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20fairly%20common%20in%20ultra-high-net-worth%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20clients%20realize%20that%20they%20are%20not%20interested%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20not%20yet%20interested%20%E2%80%94%20in%20joining%20the%20family%20business%20and%20a%20few%20individuals%20have%20chosen%20to%20leave%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20rising%20generation%20members%20are%20concerned%20about%20how%20to%20carve%20out%20a%20path%20for%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20found%20it's%20helpful%20to%20talk%20about%20this%20in%20family%20meetings%2C%20but%20also%20for%20the%20rising%20generation%20to%20be%20able%20to%20explore%20options%2C%20such%20as%20an%20internship%20or%20shadowing%20within%20the%20family%20business%2C%20to%20help%20them%20decide%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20big%20proponents%20of%20having%20a%20family%20employment%20policy%20within%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsc%2Fnew-technology-will-change-how-family-businesses-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamily%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20your%20relatives%20are%20joining%20your%20family%20business%2C%20you%20should%20require%20them%20to%20have%20a%20college%20degree%20or%20outside%20work%20experience%20to%20build%20their%20knowledge%2C%20experience%2C%20and%20credibility%20in%20their%20own%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERising%20generation%20members%20have%20told%20us%20they're%20concerned%20about%20how%20they're%20perceived%20by%20family%2C%20friends%2C%20and%20colleagues%2C%20both%20when%20working%20for%20family%20businesses%20and%20in%20other%20circumstances.%20For%20those%20working%20within%20the%20business%2C%20having%20requirements%20around%20their%20experience%20can%20boost%20their%20credibility%20at%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227e69cf3e-02f6-4936-898d-edec803f3445%5C%22%3E3.%20How%20can%20I%20navigate%20uncomfortable%20money%20dynamics%20and%20questions%20from%20friends%20and%20romantic%20partners%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20rising%20generation%20members%20interact%20with%20friends%20and%20colleagues%2C%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20uncomfortable%20questions%20about%20wealth%20and%20privilege.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20clients%20feel%20that%20they%20don't%20necessarily%20know%20how%20to%20answer%20if%20someone%20asks%20them%20a%20question%20such%20as%20%26quot%3BHow%20much%20are%20you%20worth%3F%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-does-a-trust-fund-work-basics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrust%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20worked%20with%20one%20family%20member%20who%20worked%20for%20a%20nonprofit%20in%20San%20Francisco%20and%20lived%20in%20a%20beautiful%20apartment%20that%20his%20family%20helped%20him%20purchase.%20He%20didn't%20feel%20comfortable%20having%20friends%20over%20because%20it%20would%20bring%20up%20questions%20that%20he%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20deal%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20suggested%20he%20reflect%20on%20some%20of%20the%20awkward%20money%20questions%20people%20ask%20and%20develop%20a%20short%20elevator%20speech%20that%20felt%20organic.%20He%20identified%20gratitude%20as%20a%20core%20value%2C%20and%20when%20people%20commented%20on%20the%20apartment%2C%20he'd%20respond%20with%2C%20%26quot%3BThank%20you.%20I%20wake%20up%20grateful%20every%20day.%26quot%3B%20He%20found%20it%20incredibly%20helpful%20to%20prepare%20the%20speech%20and%20share%20his%20feelings%20about%20the%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2211ee1053-6c43-4fb3-a477-f2cecbbe9091%5C%22%3E4.%20How%20can%20I%20acquire%20the%20skills%20necessary%20to%20manage%20family%20wealth%20responsibly%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20continually%20heard%20rising%20generation%20clients%20say%20they%20feel%20overwhelmed%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffather-financial-advisor-plan-to-build-generational-wealth-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanaging%20family%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20they%20didn't%20major%20in%20finance%20or%20business%20in%20college%2C%20or%20maybe%20whenever%20they%20speak%20to%20a%20parent%20or%20family%20member%2C%20they%20feel%20like%20that%20person%20is%20talking%20in%20legalese%20about%20trusts.%20They%20want%20to%20know%20where%20to%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20big%20fans%20of%20skill-building%2C%20which%20involves%20identifying%20learning%20opportunities%20to%20help%20them%20understand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fprivate-wealth-managment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewealth%20management%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20can%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-women-personal-finance-investing-stocks-wealth-savings-retirement-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvesting%3C%2Fa%3E%20smaller%20sums%20of%20money%20to%20build%20up%20to%20larger%20ones%2C%20budgeting%2C%20and%20allowances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20relevant%20exercises%20you%20can%20do%20at%20every%20age.%20Our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmlaem.fs.ml.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2FML%2FArticles%2Fpdf%2FML_PracticalIdeadEngageNextGen_BRO-08-21-0114_B_ADA.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20education%20handbook%3C%2Fa%3E%20resource%20contains%20advice%20for%20people%20aged%20five%20to%2025.%20Even%20with%20young%20children%2C%20you%20can%20talk%20about%20things%20like%20needs%20versus%20wants%2C%20credit%20cards%2C%20and%20allowances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20children%20grow%20toward%20college%20age%2C%20things%20like%20learning%20how%20to%20read%20a%20paycheck%20become%20more%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20also%20seen%20situations%20where%20there's%20a%20sudden%20death%2C%20and%20a%20pile%20of%20responsibility%20falls%20on%20a%20rising%20generation%20family%20member%20who%20feels%20completely%20overwhelmed%20while%20also%20dealing%20with%20grief.%20We're%20proponents%20of%20building%20skills%20over%20time%20to%20help%20people%20gain%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finheriting-wealth-high-net-worth-wealthy-families-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726048424000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e03424a0ff598b26660ead%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finheriting-wealth-high-net-worth-wealthy-families-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20family%20wealth%20expert%20shares%20some%20common%20questions%20that%20even%20her%20ultrawealthy%20clients%20have%20about%20managing%20inheritance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ccheong%40insider.com%20(Charissa%20Cheong)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finheriting-wealth-high-net-worth-wealthy-families-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Winning%20a%20medal%20at%20the%20Olympics%20was%20hard%2C%20but%20raising%20twins%20is%20a%20real%20endurance%20sport%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224557%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Adeline%20Gray%20with%20her%20twins%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66df3707a0ff598b2665df4e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223327%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAdeline%20Gray%20says%20having%20twins%20is%20the%20true%20endurance%20sport%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Adeline%20Gray%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAdeline%20Gray%20is%20a%20wrestler%20who%20won%20silver%20at%20the%20Tokyo%20Olympics.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20timed%20getting%20pregnant%20around%20Olympic%20cycles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENursing%20and%20raising%20twins%20is%20as%20hard%20as%20elite%20training%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.teamusa.com%2Fprofiles%2Fadeline-gray%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAdeline%2520Gray%2520is%2520a%2520six%2Cwhile%2520being%2520a%2520mother...%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EAdeline%20Gray%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20US%20Wrestling%20Team.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folympians-with-the-most-medals%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOlympic%20athlete%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20sometimes%20live%20my%20life%20in%20four-year%20cycles.%20My%20first%20Olympics%20was%20at%20the%202016%20Games%20in%20Rio.%20I%20got%20married%20right%20after%20the%20games%20and%20felt%20pressure%20to%20have%20a%20baby%20immediately%20so%20I%20could%20recover%20in%20time%20to%20train%20for%20the%202020%20Olympics.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20when%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20looked%20at%20where%20we%20were%20in%20life%2C%20we%20had%20to%20be%20honest%20that%20we%20didn't%20quite%20have%20the%20resources%20and%20support%20network%20we%20needed%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-kids-cost-raising-child-inflation-childcare-tax-exemptions-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eraise%20a%20child%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20So%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20wait%20until%20after%20the%20next%20Olympics.%20Then%2C%20the%202020%20games%20were%20pushed%20back%20a%20year%20because%20of%20COVID.%20When%20I%20finally%20competed%20in%20Tokyo%2C%20I%20took%20home%20a%20silver%20medal%2C%20which%20was%20amazing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%20home%2C%20I%20was%20so%20eager%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fwhen-do-you-ovulate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eget%20pregnant%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20My%20dad%20is%20a%20twin%2C%20and%20my%20sisters%20and%20I%20always%20joked%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwin-shares-the-downsides-of-having-a-twin-sibling-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehaving%20twins%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20As%20we%20went%20into%20the%20first%20ultrasound%2C%20my%20husband%20was%20so%20excited%20by%20the%20idea%20of%20twins%20%E2%80%94%20he%20said%20we%20had%20waited%20so%20long%20that%20we%20needed%20two%20babies%20to%20catch%20up.%20Sure%20enough%2C%20we%20could%20see%20right%20away%20there%20were%20two.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a1c0b5b8-92e6-4bbd-9692-28a9fc1b2b3d%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20trimester%20felt%20as%20hard%20as%20Olympic%20training%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20knew%20we%20could%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-mother-twins-lacking-connection-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehandle%20twins%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20There%20were%20two%20of%20us.%20I%20have%20two%20boobs%20for%20nursing.%20It%20would%20be%20tough%2C%20but%20we%20wouldn't%20be%20outnumbered.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20I%20wasn't%20prepared%20for%20was%20the%20utter%20exhaustion%20of%20the%20first%20trimester.%20I%20truly%20slept%2019%20hours%20a%20day%20sometimes.%20My%20doctors%20urged%20me%20to%20eat%20enough%20protein%20and%20get%20adequate%20rest.%20It%20felt%20exactly%20like%20elite%20athletics.%20Later%2C%20I%20was%20so%20excited%20to%20hear%20about%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FC-Yee_2OGox%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Lansinoh's%20Sponsorship%20of%20Motherhood%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20campaign%20because%20I%20felt%20like%20an%20athlete%20who%20needed%20a%20team%20behind%20her%20to%20get%20through%20pregnancy%20and%20nursing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESomewhere%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fthird-trimester%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eduring%20the%20third%20trimester%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20my%20idea%20of%20exercise%20changed%20dramatically.%20Normally%2C%20I%20train%20at%20least%20twice%20a%20day%20to%20maintain%20elite-level%20fitness.%20Suddenly%2C%20just%20getting%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20car%20became%20exercise.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELuckily%2C%20my%20pregnancy%20was%20healthy%2C%20and%20I%20was%20able%20to%20deliver%20vaginally.%20My%20twins%20(a%20boy%20and%20a%20girl%2C%20whose%20names%20I%20don't%20share%20publicly)%20were%20each%20over%20seven%20pounds%20and%20very%20healthy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22032b5368-464c-4aad-95f6-1aed6862c442%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPostpartum%2C%20I%20learned%20to%20be%20OK%20doing%20less%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20thought%20I'd%20be%20cleared%20to%20exercise%20after%20my%20six-week%20appointment%2C%20and%20I%20was%20stunned%20when%20I%20wasn't.%20The%20doctor%20told%20me%20I%20had%20severe%20diastasis%20recti%2C%20a%20separation%20in%20my%20abdominal%20muscles.%20I%20had%20access%20to%20the%20best%20doctors%2C%20trainers%2C%20and%20physical%20therapists%2C%20but%20no%20one%20could%20give%20me%20a%20clear%20answer%20for%20when%20it%20would%20resolve.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20doctor%20mentioned%20I%20might%20heal%20faster%20if%20I%20quit%20nursing.%20She%20never%20told%20me%20to%20stop%20breastfeeding%2C%20but%20I%20still%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20to%20choose%20between%20my%20career%20and%20my%20babies.%20Ultimately%2C%20I%20stuck%20with%20it%20and%20nursed%20the%20twins%20for%20almost%20a%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20was%20cleared%20for%20exercise%20after%20a%20few%20months%2C%20my%20au%20pair%20brought%20the%20twins%20to%20the%20gym.%20I%20would%20nurse%20them%2C%20then%20she%20would%20take%20them%20for%20a%20walk%20while%20I%20trained%2C%20and%20we'd%20all%20meet%20for%20lunch.%20We'd%20repeat%20that%20again%20in%20the%20afternoon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20had%20to%20give%20myself%20a%20lot%20of%20grace%20and%20accept%20where%20I%20was%20physically.%20Before%20my%20pregnancy%2C%20I%20could%20lift%20100%2C000%20pounds%20a%20day%20during%20my%20workouts.%20Postpartum%2C%20I%20was%20lucky%20to%20lift%209%2C000%20pounds.%20I%20was%20doing%20a%2010th%20of%20the%20weight%20but%20felt%20even%20more%20exhausted%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20physical%20demands%20of%20nursing%20twins.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20learned%20to%20be%20OK%20doing%20less%2C%20but%20to%20still%20maintain%20the%20discipline%20to%20show%20up%20day%20after%20day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b69343be-15ab-4568-b2cc-cf94c7a9cb0f%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESometimes%20I%20travel%20for%20competitions%20with%20just%201%20child%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20twins%20turned%202%20in%20July.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20being%20a%20twin%20mom%20is%20easier%20than%20raising%20singletons%20because%20you%20learn%20so%20quickly.%20Recently%2C%20my%20daughter%20gave%20me%20a%20funny%20look%20and%20then%20vomited%20all%20over%20me.%20When%20I%20saw%20the%20same%20look%20on%20my%20son's%20face%2C%20I%20ran%20him%20to%20the%20bathroom.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20wrestler%2C%20I'm%20excellent%20at%20diaper%20changes.%20I%20know%20that%20game%2C%20and%20the%20twins%20have%20accepted%20they%20can't%20get%20away%20from%20mom.%20We%20still%20use%20the%20au%20pair%20for%20childcare%2C%20but%20when%20I%20travel%20I%20sometimes%20bring%20just%20one%20of%20the%20kids%2C%20leaving%20the%20other%20with%20my%20parents.%20Logistically%2C%20having%20one%20toddler%20is%20much%20easier.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20spring%2C%20I%20competed%20in%20the%20Olympic%20trials%2C%20coming%20in%20second%20in%20my%20weight%20class.%20However%2C%20because%20I%20was%20an%20alternate%2C%20I%20didn't%20compete%20in%20Paris.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI'm%20still%20open%20to%20competing%20in%20LA%20in%202026%2C%20but%20I'm%20embracing%20a%20new%20role%20on%20the%20national%20wrestling%20team.%20I%20still%20have%20a%20lot%20to%20give%2C%20even%20if%20I'm%20not%20in%20the%20top%20spot.%20I%20want%20the%20younger%20women%20on%20the%20team%20to%20realize%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20put%20their%20lives%20on%20hold.%20They%20can%20still%20get%20married%20and%20have%20babies%20while%20chasing%20their%20athletic%20dreams.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folympian-adeline-gray-raising-twins-harder-than-the-olympics-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726048202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66df3731a0ff598b2665dfcd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folympian-adeline-gray-raising-twins-harder-than-the-olympics-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20wrestler%2C%20who%20won%20a%20silver%20medal%20in%20the%20Tokyo%20Olympics%2C%20timed%20her%20pregnancy%20around%20Olympic%20cycles.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Burch)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folympian-adeline-gray-raising-twins-harder-than-the-olympics-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Millennials%20loved%20Megabus.%20So%20why%20did%20it%20go%20mega-bust%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Megabus%20falling%20off%20a%20cliff%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d8aab814a5cd1fcc8d5f8f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrivate%20equity%20and%20a%20pandemic%20were%20a%20recipe%20for%20disaster%20for%20Megabus.%3Cp%3ESmith%20Collection%2FGado%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20were%20in%20college%20over%20the%20past%2020%20years%20or%20so%2C%20you%20might%20have%20some%20fond%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20so%20fond%20%E2%80%94%20memories%20of%20Megabus.%20The%20blue%20double-decker%20buses%20with%20power%20outlets%20that%20worked%20most%20of%20the%20time%20and%20WiFi%20that%20worked%20rarely%20have%20for%20years%20been%20an%20important%2C%20if%20imperfect%2C%20way%20for%20budget-conscious%20travelers%20to%20get%20from%20point%20A%20to%20point%20B.%20The%20trip%20wasn't%20always%20pretty%20%E2%80%94%20you%20often%20got%20plopped%20in%20front%20of%20an%20obnoxious%20phone%20talker%20or%20wound%20up%20traumatized%20by%20the%20bathroom%20%E2%80%94%20but%20in%20general%2C%20you%20got%20where%20you%20needed%20to%20go%20for%20a%20good%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%20Megabus%20is%20in%20trouble.%20Its%20parent%20company%2C%20Coach%20USA%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.coachusa.com%2Fnews-and-media%2Fcoach-usa-initiates-voluntary-chapter-eleven%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20for%20bankruptcy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June.%20Megabus%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fus.megabus.com%2Froutechanges%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehanding%20over%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20routes%20between%20cities%20in%20the%20Northeast%20to%20other%20operators%20and%20discontinuing%20some%20routes%20in%20the%20South%20altogether.%20If%20you%20take%20a%20look%20at%20Megabus'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fmegabus%2Fwith_replies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20Twitter%20activity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you'll%20notice%20the%20social-media%20manager's%20main%20job%20lately%20seems%20to%20be%20explaining%20to%20people%20that%2C%20yes%2C%20their%20trip%20may%20have%20been%20canceled%2C%20but%20no%2C%20the%20company%20has%20not%20gone%20out%20of%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20what's%20happened%20with%20Megabus%20has%20to%20do%20with%20macro%20factors%20outside%20its%20control.%20The%20pandemic%20was%20devastating%20for%20the%20already%20struggling%20intercity%20bus%20industry.%20The%20federal%20government%20didn't%20step%20in%20to%20try%20to%20shore%20up%20the%20sector%20like%20it%20did%20with%2C%20say%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairlines-coronavirus-bailout-senate-stock-buybacks-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20airlines%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20even%20before%20the%20global%20catastrophe%2C%20there%20was%20another%20particular%20factor%20that%20helped%20put%20Megabus%20on%20its%20current%20downward%20trajectory%3A%20private-equity%20ownership.%20Variant%20Equity%20Advisors%2C%20a%20Los%20Angeles-based%20PE%20fund%2C%20acquired%20Coach%20USA%20in%202019%20for%20%24271.4%20million%20and%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fred-lobster-endless-shrimp-bankruptcy-private-equity-debt-real-estate-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20private%20equity%20is%20wont%20to%20do%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20loaded%20the%20bus%20operator%20up%20with%20debt%20the%20company%20couldn't%20service%20once%20travel%20came%20to%20a%20halt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20private-equity%20firm%20buying%20bus%20carriers%20right%20before%20a%20global%20pandemic%20was%20not%20the%20best%20timing%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrew%20Savikas%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Wanderu%2C%20a%20travel-search%20platform%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20sounds%20kind%20of%20strange%20to%20describe%20a%20dirt-cheap%20bus%20operation%20this%20way%2C%20but%20the%20original%20idea%20behind%20Megabus%20was%20to%20make%20the%20service%20sort%20of%20hip.%20Stagecoach%20Group%2C%20a%20UK-based%20travel%20company%2C%20first%20launched%20Megabus%20in%20the%20UK%20in%202003%20and%20then%20brought%20it%20to%20the%20US%20in%202006.%20It%20was%20an%20upgrade%20from%20the%20Chinatown%20buses%2C%20which%20also%20eschewed%20terminals%20and%20instead%20did%20curbside%20pickup%20as%20they%20shuttled%20from%20city%20to%20city%20but%20often%20offered%20a%20lower-quality%20experience.%20Megabus%20had%20what%20at%20the%20time%20were%20considered%20fancy%20amenities%20like%20outlets%20and%20online%20ticketing%2C%20and%20above%20all%2C%20it%20maintained%20a%20low%20price%20point.%20Both%20Megabus%20and%20its%20rival%20BoltBus%2C%20which%20Greyhound%20and%20Peter%20Pan%20launched%20in%202008%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2Farchive%2F6904383%2Fbeating-4-gas-with-a-1-bus%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewould%20lure%20people%20in%20by%20advertising%20%241%20tickets%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20number%20was%20largely%20a%20gimmick%20%E2%80%94%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20tickets%20on%20each%20bus%20were%20a%20buck%20%E2%80%94%20but%20in%20general%2C%20prices%20were%20pretty%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMegabus%20was%20the%20disruptor%20in%20the%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Stepovy%2C%20the%20director%20of%20partnerships%20for%20North%20America%20at%20Busbud%2C%20a%20bus-ticketing%20platform%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20the%20first%20to%20really%20get%20away%20from%20bus%20terminals%20and%20really%20go%20curbside%20and%20really%20focus%20on%20students%20and%20online%20and%20just%20kind%20of%20being%20that%20cool%20brand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20ate%20it%20up.%20High%20gas%20prices%20pushing%20up%20the%20price%20of%20air%20and%20car%20travel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbusiness.time.com%2F2012%2F11%2F15%2Freinventing-the-wheels-megabus-and-boltbus%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emade%20bus%20travel%20a%20convenient%2C%20affordable%20alternative%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20financial%20market%20that%20left%20many%20young%20people%20on%20their%20heels.%20Megabus'%20strategy%20of%20offering%20a%20slightly%20upgraded%20experience%20let%20it%20escape%20the%20dingy%2C%20sketchy%20reputation%20buses%20had.%20(Seriously%2C%20ask%20your%20friendly%20local%20millennial%20for%20a%20bus%20story%2C%20they%20probably%20have%20a%20good%20one.)%20Along%20with%20Greyhound%2C%20Megabus%20became%20one%20of%20the%20two%20mega-carriers%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bus%20market%20started%20to%20weaken%20in%20the%20mid-2010s.%20Gas%20prices%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgas-prices-hit-6-year-low-2015-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efell%20significantly%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20late%202015%20and%202016%2C%20making%20alternative%20and%20perhaps%20more%20preferable%20modes%20of%20transportation%2C%20like%20flying%20and%20driving%2C%20cheaper.%20The%20German%20operator%20FlixBus%20also%20launched%20in%20the%20US%20in%202018%2C%20adding%20another%20competitor%20to%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20magic%20faded%2C%26quot%3B%20Joseph%20Schwieterman%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20public%20service%20at%20DePaul%20University%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BSuddenly%2C%20there's%20three%20national%20carriers.%20It%20might've%20been%20one%20too%20many.%20So%20Megabus%20gradually%20cut%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStagecoach%20announced%20in%20late%202018%20that%20it%20would%20sell%20its%20struggling%20US%20division%20to%20Variant%20in%20a%20deal%20that%20closed%20in%20spring%202019.%20We%20all%20know%20what%20happened%20the%20next%20year%3A%20The%20pandemic%20ground%20travel%2C%20including%20on%20buses%2C%20to%20a%20stop.%20In%20its%20bankruptcy%20filings%2C%20Coach%20USA%20said%20bus%20ridership%20in%202020%20fell%20by%2090%25%2C%20and%20by%202023%2C%20had%20only%20recovered%20to%2045%25%20of%20its%20pre-pandemic%20level.%20That%20made%20it%20hard%20for%20the%20company%20to%20pay%20on%20its%20private-equity-induced%20debt%2C%20most%20of%20which%20it%20still%20owes.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbankruptcy-proxy-api.dowjones.ai%2Fcases%2FDelaware_Bankruptcy_Court%2F1--24-bk-11258%2FCoach_USA_Inc%2Fdocs%2F15.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecourt%20filings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Coach%20USA%20had%20%24197.8%20million%20in%20debt%20when%20it%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%2C%20including%20%24146.6%20million%20on%20the%20loan%20that%20funded%20the%20Variant%20deal%20and%20%2437.7%20million%20on%20a%20pandemic-era%20relief%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Megabus%20brand%20isn't%20going%20away%20entirely.%20Coach%20USA%20is%20selling%20off%20some%20of%20its%20lines%2C%20IP%2C%20and%20retail%20operations%20to%20a%20holding%20company.%20Megabus%20is%20handing%20some%20of%20its%20routes%20to%20companies%20such%20as%20Peter%20Pan%20and%20Fullington%20Trailways%20while%20also%20shuttering%20some%20routes%20altogether.%20You%20can%20still%20book%20bus%20travel%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMegabus.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMegabus.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20if%20you%20look%20closely%2C%20you'll%20see%20many%20of%20the%20buses%20that%20show%20up%20are%20operated%20by%20a%20different%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Megabus%20was%20ahead%20of%20the%20curve%20with%20the%20power%20outlets%20and%20the%20online%20booking%20and%20the%20WiFi%2C%20everybody%20else%20has%20caught%20up.%20And%20one%20of%20the%20company's%20more%20distinctive%20features%20%E2%80%94%20those%20double-decker%20buses%20%E2%80%94%20hasn't%20really%20worked%20in%20the%20US.%20Passengers%20don't%20seem%20to%20love%20them%20because%20the%20storage%20space%20they%20offer%20is%20limited%2C%20and%20some%20people%20are%20uncomfortable%20not%20being%20able%20to%20see%20the%20driver.%20They%20can%20be%20extra%20expensive%20to%20operate%20and%20so%20big%20that%2C%20operationally%2C%20they%20don't%20always%20make%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Megabus%20double-deckers%20are%20mostly%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwieterman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoach%20USA%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%20Megabus%20and%20Variant%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20intercity%20bus%20industry%20is%20not%20in%20complete%20disarray%2C%20but%20things%20are%20not%20going%20great%20there.%20It's%20still%20digging%20out%20of%20a%20pandemic-sized%20hole%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flas.depaul.edu%2Fcenters-and-institutes%2Fchaddick-institute-for-metropolitan-development%2Fresearch-and-publications%2FDocuments%2F2023%2520Outlook%2520for%2520the%2520Intercity%2520Bus%2520Industry.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eridership%20is%20only%20about%2080%25%20to%2085%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20where%20it%20was%20before.%20It%20has%20benefited%20from%20some%20of%20the%20pent-up%20demand%20for%20travel%20that%20built%20up%20in%202020%20and%202021%2C%20but%20not%20to%20the%20extent%20other%20industries%20have%20as%20many%20Americans%20have%20opted%20to%20travel%20further%20afield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20saw%20revenge%20travel%2C%20and%20maybe%20people%20were%20flying%20to%20places%20when%20they%20hadn't%20had%20a%20chance%20to%20go%20anywhere%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20Michael%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20United%20Motorcoach%20Association%2C%20an%20industry%20trade%20group%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20take%20a%20bus%20to%20Asia%20unless%20you're%20already%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20leisure%20travelers%2C%20remote%20work%20also%20means%20people%20who%20might%20have%20taken%20intercity%20buses%20or%20coaches%20to%20commute%20aren't%20doing%20so%20as%20frequently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMegabus%20may%20be%20the%20highest-profile%20COVID%20casualty%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20the%20only%20one.%20Michael%20said%20there%20were%20about%203%2C000%20licensed%20bus%20and%20motorcoach%20companies%20before%20the%20pandemic.%20Now%2C%20that%20number%20is%20around%201%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHalf%20of%20the%20industry%20is%20gone%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20smaller%20companies%20that%20were%20impacted.%20The%20larger%20ones%20tend%20to%20have%20made%20it%20through%2C%20with%20some%20exceptions%20obviously%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoltBus%20is%20gone%20now%2C%20too.%20Its%20parent%20company%2C%20Greyhound%2C%20shut%20down%20its%20operations%20in%202021.%20Greyhound%20itself%20was%20bought%20for%20%2476%20million%20that%20same%20year%20by%20FlixMobility%20(of%20FlixBus%20fame).%20Kai%20Boysan%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Flix%20North%20America%2C%20said%20BoltBus%20was%20shut%20down%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic%20and%20as%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20strategic%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBolt%20Bus%20was%20initially%20launched%20to%20target%20a%20specific%20market%20segment%20with%20a%20low-cost%2C%20no-frills%20service.%20However%2C%20as%20we%20assessed%20the%20long-term%20strategy%20for%20Greyhound%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20our%20resources%20would%20be%20better%20used%20by%20focusing%20on%20the%20Greyhound%20brand%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20changing%20consumer%20preferences%2C%20the%20industry%20is%20also%20dealing%20with%20problems%20on%20the%20operational%20side%2C%20such%20as%20rising%20costs%20for%20parts%20and%20a%20shortage%20of%20both%20drivers%20and%20mechanics.%20Bus%20industry%20insiders%20also%20note%20that%20they're%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.governing.com%2Fnow%2Fintercity-bus-service-gets-no-respect-from-government%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etreated%20as%20an%20afterthought%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20policymakers%20even%20though%20they%20carry%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20people%20each%20year.%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20intercity%20buses%20didn't%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20support%20from%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20unlike%20airlines%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frailroads.dot.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2Fus-transportation-secretary-pete-buttigieg-announces-169-billion-amtrak-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrains%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20companies%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20relatively%20small%2C%20independent%2C%20family-owned%20businesses%20who%20were%20waiting%20in%20line%20with%20everybody%20else%20for%20the%20kind%20of%20assistance%20that%20they%20could%20get%20to%20get%20through%20COVID%2C%26quot%3B%20Savikas%2C%20from%20Wanderu%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFred%20Ferguson%2C%20the%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20American%20Bus%20Association%2C%20told%20me%20that%20funding%20the%20intercity%20bus%20industry%20does%20get%20from%20the%20federal%20government%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20to%20help%20them%20service%20less%20populous%20areas%20%E2%80%94%20isn't%20keeping%20up%20with%20rising%20costs.%20He%20added%20that%20some%20localities%20are%20also%20pushing%20back%20against%20bus%20terminals%20because%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20this%20perception%20that%20if%20you%20have%20a%20bus%20terminal%2C%20you're%20somehow%20going%20to%20attract%20people%20who%20you%20don't%20want%20in%20your%20towns.%26quot%3B%20It's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FNIMBY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENIMBYism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20for%20the%20bus%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20happens%20is%20it's%20the%20end%20consumer%2C%20and%20more%20times%20than%20not%20the%20end%20consumer%20who%20can't%20afford%20a%20plane%20ticket%2C%20who's%20getting%20left%20behind%2C%26quot%3B%20Ferguson%20said.%20%26quot%3BMegabus%20and%20all%20that%2C%20it's%20just%20a%20microcosm%20for%20all%20these%20bigger%20problems%20that%20we're%20seeing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20the%20public%20sector%20that's%20exacerbating%20the%20terminals%20issue%3B%20it's%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20too.%20In%202022%2C%20Greyhound's%20former%20parent%20company%2C%20FirstGroup%2C%20sold%2033%20of%20its%20bus%20stations%20to%20Twenty%20Lake%20Holdings%2C%20a%20commercial%20real-estate%20investor.%20It's%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20Alden%20Global%20Capital%2C%20a%20hedge%20fund%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2021%2F10%2F18%2F1046952430%2Fthe-consequences-of-when-a-hedge-fund-buys-newspapers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enotorious%20for%20buying%20up%20and%20gutting%20local%20newspapers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Twenty%20Lake%20can%20make%20more%20money%20using%20the%20real%20estate%20for%20something%20else%2C%20so%20many%20of%20those%20terminals%20have%20already%20closed%2C%20moved%2C%20or%20are%20expected%20to%20do%20so%20soon%2C%20including%20in%20Philadelphia%2C%20Dallas%2C%20and%20Chicago.%20Wanderu%20estimates%20that%20the%20closures%20will%20affect%2065%25%20of%20bus%20travelers%20in%20and%20out%20of%20Philadelphia%2C%2050%25%20in%20Dallas%20and%20Chicago%2C%20and%20virtually%20everyone%20in%20and%20out%20of%20Cleveland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey've%20been%20willing%20to%20talk%20to%20the%20bus%20lines%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwieterman%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20just%20saying%2C%20'You're%20out%20of%20here%2C%20new%20chapter.'%20They're%20reportedly%20just%20saying%2C%20'We%20paid%20lots%20of%20money%20for%20these%20terminals%20and%20we%20have%20to%20be%20financially%20rewarded%20for%20our%20investments.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty%20Lake%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20the%20intercity%20bus%20business%20is%20facing%20some%20headwinds%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20involvement%20of%20private%20equity%20and%20hedge%20funds%20is%20not%20helping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20jonesing%20to%20hop%20on%20a%20bus%20to%20Boston%20or%20New%20York%20for%20the%20weekend%2C%20you%20have%20options.%20There's%20still%20Peter%20Pan%2C%20Greyhound%2C%20and%20Flix%2C%20plus%20a%20fair%20number%20of%20smaller%20regional%20and%20local%20carriers%20that%20will%20get%20you%20where%20you're%20going.%20But%20your%20options%20will%20most%20likely%20be%20more%20limited%20than%20before.%20They%20might%20also%20be%20more%20expensive%2C%20just%20like%20everything.%20I%20recently%20bought%20bus%20tickets%20to%20Atlantic%20City%20for%20the%20weekend%2C%20and%20I%20was%20initially%20convinced%20I'd%20made%20some%20sort%20of%20mistake%2C%20given%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%20Wanderu%2C%20the%20average%20price%20of%20one-way%20bus%20trips%20across%20the%20US%20for%20the%20summer%20travel%20period%20from%20Memorial%20Day%20through%20Labor%20Day%20increased%20from%20%2445%20in%202020%20to%20%2468.73%20in%202023%2C%20though%20prices%20dipped%20slightly%20in%202024%20to%20%2464.01.%20Wanderu%20noted%20that%20train%20prices%20remain%20higher%2C%20going%20from%20%2468.16%20in%202020%20to%20%2499.95%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20in%20the%20bus%20industry%20I%20spoke%20to%20were%20relatively%20hopeful%20about%20its%20future.%20They%20noted%20that%20business%20for%20charter%20operations%2C%20like%20bringing%20a%20high-school%20football%20team%20to%20a%20game%20or%20getting%20workers%20to%20a%20corporate%20retreat%2C%20was%20starting%20to%20pick%20up.%20Most%20expected%20ridership%20to%20bounce%20back%20over%20the%20next%20couple%20of%20years.%20Boysan%2C%20from%20FlixBus%2C%20said%20its%20ridership%20had%20increased%20by%2036%25%20from%202022%20to%202023%2C%20and%20they're%20seeing%20consumers%20gravitate%20toward%20%26quot%3Bbudget%20options%26quot%3B%20given%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTravelers%20are%20more%20price-sensitive%20and%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20save%20money%20without%20sacrificing%20convenience%20or%20comfort%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20trend%20is%20especially%20pronounced%20among%20solo%20travelers%2C%20middle-class%20travelers%2C%20and%20those%20from%20lower-income%20brackets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20getting%20back%20to%20pre-pandemic%20levels%20isn't%20a%20total%20fix%2C%20given%20the%20steady%20ridership%20decline%20that%20predated%20the%20shutdowns.%20No%20one%20seemed%20to%20have%20a%20great%20answer%20on%20how%20to%20reverse%20the%20industry's%20long-term%20problems%2C%20but%20many%20companies%20are%20experimenting%20with%20some%20options.%20Savikas%2C%20from%20Wanderu%2C%20said%20some%20carriers%20are%20implementing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-dynamic-pricing-surge-cost-fatigue-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eairline-like%20dynamic%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20ticket%20prices%20change%20around%20supply-and-demand%20dynamics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20is%20to%20make%20it%20more%20economically%20sustainable%20all%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20emphasized%20that%20bus%20travel%20can%20be%20environmentally%20sustainable%2C%20too%2C%20compared%20to%20everyone%20driving%20their%20own%20cars%20or%20flying.%20%26quot%3BBuses%20actually%20are%20a%20pretty%20green%20way%20to%20get%20around.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20bug%20travel%20may%20never%20be%20what%20it%20once%20was.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20questions%2C%20probably%2C%20if%20there%20will%20be%20full%20recovery%20in%20certain%20sectors%2C%20in%20certain%20regions%2C%26quot%3B%20Stepovy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20heyday%20of%20hungover%2020-somethings%20dragging%20themselves%20onto%20a%20Megabus%20after%20a%20slightly%20too%20fun%20weekend%20is%20in%20the%20rearview%20mirror.%20But%20there's%20some%20sort%20of%20iteration%20of%20it%20ahead%2C%20too%2C%20just%20not%20on%20a%20blue%20double-decker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmegabus-coach-usa-bankruptcy-what-happened-greyhound-private-equity-debt-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726048081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d8aad414a5cd1fcc8d5fa2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmegabus-coach-usa-bankruptcy-what-happened-greyhound-private-equity-debt-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Megabus%20was%20the%20favorite%20cheap%20travel%20option%20for%20millennials.%20Then%20it%20ran%20out%20of%20gas.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmegabus-coach-usa-ban