gages%2C%20credit%2C%20and%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmarkets%2Finterest-rates%2Fcme-fedwatch-tool.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECME%20FedWatch%20Tool%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there's%20a%20roughly%2075%25%20chance%20that%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Markets%20Committee%20will%20decrease%20interest%20rates%20by%2025%20basis%20points%20and%20a%2025%25%20chance%20the%20Fed%20will%20decrease%20interest%20rates%20by%2050%20basis%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20said%20that%20small%20business%20owners%20are%20poised%20to%20benefit%20regardless%20of%20the%20size%20of%20the%20cut%20and%20should%20remain%20hopeful%20about%20future%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFalling%20interest%20rates%20are%20going%20to%20make%20credit%20easier%20to%20acquire%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20a%20small%20business%2C%20whether%20you%20need%20a%20loan%20for%20a%20capital%20investment%20or%20a%20loan%20for%20working%20capital%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20easier%20to%20acquire%2C%20steadily.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224365bdec-7a60-4f9a-8f5f-283ee993e9e1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20brightening%20economic%20outlook%20goes%20beyond%20interest%20rates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEntrepreneurs%20have%20filed%20a%20record%2019%20million%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhome.treasury.gov%2Fnews%2Ffeatured-stories%2Fsmall-business-and-entrepreneurship-in-the-post-covid-expansion%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520post%252Dpandemic%2520economy%252C%2520with%2Csince%2520the%2520end%2520of%25202020.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapplications%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20new%20businesses%20in%20the%20past%20four%20years%2C%20and%20business%20applications%20remain%20elevated%20above%20pre-pandemic%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20small%20businesses%20created%2071%25%20of%20net%20new%20jobs%20since%202019%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhome.treasury.gov%2Fnews%2Ffeatured-stories%2Fsmall-business-and-entrepreneurship-in-the-post-covid-expansion%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520post%252Dpandemic%2520economy%252C%2520with%2Csince%2520the%2520end%2520of%25202020.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETreasury%20Department%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20small%20business%20economy%20can%20be%20volatile%2C%20and%20applications%20don't%20always%20translate%20into%20successful%20projects%2C%20according%20to%20Powell%2C%20well-managed%20businesses%20are%20in%20for%20an%20era%20of%20stable%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20Powell%20is%20bullish%20that%20small%20businesses%20are%20poised%20for%20a%20productivity%20boom%20like%20in%20the%201990s%20when%20there%20was%20a%20surge%20in%20tech%20startups%20surrounding%20the%20development%20of%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20said%20that%20similar%20to%20the%201990s%2C%20the%20US%20economy%20has%20seen%20strong%20year-over-year%20growth%20in%20corporate%20profit%2C%20stock%20market%20growth%2C%20and%20increases%20in%20labor%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20labor%20productivity%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20was%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fopub%2Fted%2F2024%2Fproductivity-increased-2-7-percent-from-second-quarter-2023-to-second-quarter-2024.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNonfarm%2520business%2520sector%2520labor%2520productivity%2Chours%2520worked%2520rose%25200.7%2520percent.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2.7%25%20year-over-year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20an%20overlooked%20yet%20positive%20sign%20for%20economic%20growth%2C%20Powell%20said.%20He%20also%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-use-ai-save-time-work-best-ways-use-chatgpt-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20will%20further%20contribute%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20productivity%20boom%20if%20entrepreneurs%20can%20learn%20to%20use%20it%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fhow-use-ai-same-time-work-chatgpt-claude-jasper-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esave%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20said%20solid%20economic%20growth%20is%20another%20positive%20sign%20for%20small%20businesses.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bea.gov%2Fdata%2Fgdp%2Fgross-domestic-product%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGross%2520Domestic%2520Product%2520(Second%2520Estimate%2CPreliminary%2520Estimate)%252C%2520Second%2520Quarter%25202024%26amp%3Btext%3DReal%2520gross%2520domestic%2520product%2520(GDP%2Cthe%2520calculation%2520of%2520GDP%252C%2520increased.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20real%20GDP%20increased%203%25%20year-over-year%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20many%20small%20businesses%20aren't%20feeling%20the%20relief%20yet.%20According%20to%20the%20National%20Federation%20of%20Independent%20Businesses%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nfib.com%2Fsurveys%2Fsmall-business-economic-trends%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmall%20business%20confidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20dipped%20in%20August.%20Yet%2C%20Powell%20said%20the%20economic%20data%20points%20to%20brighter%20days%20ahead%20despite%20the%20dip%20in%20optimism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20economy%20is%20much%20better%20than%20it%20feels%2C%20but%20our%20emotions%20lead%20us%20astray%20in%20terms%20of%20our%20impressions%2C%20even%20as%20business%20owners%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEconomic%20indicators%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-outlook-data-points-to-soft-landing-no-recession-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoint%20to%20a%20soft%20landing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20small%20business%20owners%20who%20are%20struggling%20with%20high%20rates%20just%20need%20to%20make%20it%20through%20these%20next%20few%20months%2C%20Powell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20they%20should%20be%20fearful%20of%20is%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20get%20too%20pessimistic%2C%20and%20they're%20going%20to%20make%20emotional%20business%20decisions%2C%20and%20they're%20going%20to%20lose%20out%20on%20what%20could%20be%20several%20years%20of%20upcoming%20prosperity%20driven%20by%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESean%20Higgins%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20finance%20at%20the%20Kellogg%20School%20of%20Management%20at%20Northwestern%20University%2C%20similarly%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20could%20be%20particularly%20positive%20for%20small%20business%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20small%20businesses%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20credit-constrained%2C%20so%20changes%20in%20interest%20rates%20are%20particularly%20influential%20for%20business%20owners'%20management%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20often%20the%20ones%20that%20can%20be%20more%20affected%20by%20or%20benefit%20more%20once%20rates%20come%20back%20down%2C%20relative%20to%20larger%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Higgins%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHiggins%20said%20that%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20would%20create%20access%20to%20cheaper%20credit%2C%20enabling%20small%20business%20owners%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20tech%20startups%20or%20mom-and-pop%20shops%20on%20Main%20Street%20%E2%80%94%20to%20invest%20further%20in%20growing%20their%20businesses%20or%20funding%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20small%20business%20owner%20who%20has%20experienced%20a%20recent%20change%20in%20sales%20or%20hiring%3F%20This%20reporter%20wants%20to%20hear%20from%20you.%20Please%20reach%20out%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajtowfighi%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejtowfighi%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-smal