s%20technology%20fortunes%20are%20notoriously%20volatile.%20Musk%20was%20worth%20just%20%24164%20billion%20as%20recently%20as%20April%2C%20while%20Bezos%20was%20worth%20a%20little%20less%20in%20early%20January%20than%20Zuckerberg%20is%20now.%20A%20few%20bad%20days%20for%20Tesla%20and%20Amazon%2C%20and%20a%20few%20good%20ones%20for%20Meta%2C%20would%20allow%20Zuckerberg%20to%20seize%20the%20top%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20true%20that%20Meta%2C%20Tesla%2C%20and%20Amazon%20trade%20similarly%20as%20all%20three%20are%20mega-cap%20US%20tech%20stocks%2C%20meaning%20Zuckerberg%2C%20Musk%2C%20and%20Bezos'%20fortunes%20tend%20to%20rise%20and%20fall%20in%20tandem.%20But%20a%20bad%20earnings%20report%2C%20a%20bombshell%20lawsuit%2C%20an%20antitrust%20investigation%2C%20or%20a%20disaster%20of%20any%20kind%20could%20knock%20Musk%20and%20Bezos%20below%20Zuckerberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20could%20also%20climb%20to%20the%20peak%20if%20Musk%20and%20Bezos%20make%20some%20large%20philanthropic%20donations.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20only%20reason%20that%20Warren%20Buffett%20isn't%20the%20richest%20person%20on%20the%20planet%20with%20a%20%24300%20billion-plus%20net%20worth%20is%20that%20he's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-elon-musk-tesla-stock-wealth-philanthropy-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edonated%20more%20than%20half%20his%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%20stock%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Meta%20chief%20has%20been%20outpacing%20Musk%20and%20Bezos%20in%20wealth%20accumulation%20this%20year%2C%20putting%20him%20on%20track%20to%20overtake%20them.%20His%20%2451%20billion%20gain%20this%20year%20far%20surpasses%20their%20respective%20increases%20of%20%2419%20billion%20and%20%2425%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%2C%2040%2C%20probably%20has%20more%20time%20than%20Musk%2C%2053%2C%20and%20Bezos%2C%2060%2C%20to%20grow%20his%20already%20vast%20fortune.%20Buffett%20amassed%20over%2099%25